The way that this is overcome is that most garbage collectors only permit direct pointers to an object rather than to a particular field inside an object. For example, there&#x27;s no Java equivalent to this C:<p><pre><code>  void a(int *b)
  {
      *b = 5;
  }

  struct c
  {
      int d;
  };

  int main()
  {
      struct c foo;
      a(&foo.d); // no way to do this in Java!
      printf(&quot;%lu\n&quot;, (unsigned long)foo.d);
  }</code></pre>
